interactions.flavorLineOne: "That's it. Had to pare down some of the weirder features. Still works as a stellar sextant, cable splitter, avionics trawl, pneumatic drill, compass aligner... anyway. Enjoy the gun part." —Banshee-44
Banshee's old hands rove over the Ace of Spades, sliding new pieces into place, closing a polished unscored chassis over its perfectly tuned mechanisms. It's done. The Ace of Spades is yours.
Banshee looks like he recognizes what you've brought him, but you can't be sure. There's no mistaking the gratitude in his eyes, though.
The Gunsmith has a delivery for you: an experimental prototype weapon from Omolon foundry.
Banshee-44 blinks and stares at the gift, then takes it before you can question him.

Banshee is quiet for a while, then he says, "Say. I don't mind lookin' at this for you, but I'm gonna have to tell Ikora about it, all right?"

You nod. "You might as well throw this away and start from scratch," Banshee mumbles. "But… If you're really determined…"

By the time he sends you on your way with a detailed shopping list, he's forgotten the conversation entirely.

Banshee-44's eyes burn brightly as he speaks of repairing the Ace of Spades. But he can't do it alone. He'll need some biorhythmic data from you—and some parts from the secret caches Cayde hid across the system.
"Almost got it. Still need. Huh. Kind of a strange one. Still need some more data. For the tracker. Keep an open mind." —Banshee-44
"Good start. That's a good start. Need more details, though. Ins and outs. Lots of Scouts run on MIDA principles. Crack them open. We'll see what we can find." —Banshee-44
Banshee-44 forged Cayde's favorite gun, the Ace of Spades. He can't bear the thought of that prized piece in Uldren's hand.

interactions.flavorLineOne: "MIDA. MIDA. Old name. Almost as old as me. Lost a bunch of my schematics when the Tower went down. Could recreate one for you. If that's the kind of thing you're into." —Banshee-44
